# Philly Steak Stuffed Peppers
## Ingrediants
* 2x Green peppers, halved and de-seeded
* 8oz serloin
* 1 onion sliced
* 3 mushrooms diced
* 6 slice,s bacon shopped
* Salt and Pepper to taste
* 4oz cream cheese
* 1/4 cup nutritional yeast powder
* 1tsp Garlic Powder
* 1tsp Onion Powder

## Steps
1. Place peppers on plate and covered with platic wrap
2. Microwave on high for 3 mins until soft
3. Cook bacon, onion, mushroom on a skillet until bacon is almost done
4. Add sirlion and cook through throughly

5. Put cream cheese in a microwave safe bowl and microwave in 30s intervals until cream cheese is soft
6. Add nutritional yeast and garlic power, stir thouruhly
7. Drain water from peppers and stuff with steak mixture
8. Top with the cheese mixture
9. Place peppers in a pie plate and broil on high for 5-10mins until brown

From Code Red Cookbook 3rd ed
